TITLE: Downloading Generated Image (Python)
DESCRIPTION: Python function to download an image generated by Pollinations.AI using the API. It takes a prompt as input and saves the resulting image to a file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pollinations/pollinations/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import requests

def download_image(prompt):
    url = f"https://pollinations.ai/p/{prompt}"
    response = requests.get(url)
    with open('generated_image.jpg', 'wb') as file:
        file.write(response.content)
    print('Image downloaded!')

download_image("conceptual_isometric_world_of_pollinations_ai_surreal_hyperrealistic_digital_garden")
```

